There are three people sitting in a room - Alice, Bob, and Charlie. They need to decide on the temperature to set on the air conditioner. Everyone has a demand each:
Alice wants the temperature to be at least A degrees. Bob wants the temperature to be at most B degrees. Charlie wants the temperature to be at least C degrees.
Can they all agree on some temperature, or not?




#include <stdio.h>

int main() {
	int A,B,C;
	scanf("%d%d%d",&A,&B,&C);
	if(A>B||C>B) {
	    printf("YES");
	} else {
	    printf("NO");
	}

}
